<Project Sdk="Microsoft.NET.Sdk">

  <Import Project="../../package.props" />

  <PropertyGroup>
    <TargetFrameworks>net8.0;net10.0</TargetFrameworks>
    <Description>
      A little utility to perform design-time builds of .NET projects without
      having to think too hard about it. This extension library adds support
      for creating a Roslyn workspace from Buildalyzer.
    </Description>
    <PackageId>Buildalyzer.Workspaces</PackageId>
    <PackageValidationBaselineVersion>8.0.0</PackageValidationBaselineVersion>
    <PackageReleaseNotes>
      <![CDATA[
ToBeReleased
- Target .NET 10.0. #252
- Drop .NET 6.0.
- Upgrade Microsoft.CodeAnalysis.Workspaces (Roslyn) to 5.6.0.
- The workspace now includes analyzer config documents (.editorconfig/.globalconfig, including the SDK-generated ones), matching MSBuildWorkspace.
- Workspace documents now carry their logical folder path (Document.Folders), derived from the file's location relative to the project directory, matching MSBuildWorkspace.
- The workspace project now sets its reference-assembly output path (Project.OutputRefFilePath) from TargetRefPath.
- Document source text is now hashed with the project's ChecksumAlgorithm (SHA256 by default) instead of always SHA1, matching MSBuildWorkspace and the compiler.
- Document source text now preserves the file's own encoding (BOM-detected, UTF-8 default) instead of being forced to UTF-16, matching MSBuildWorkspace.
- The workspace project now honours AssemblyName and RootNamespace (Project.AssemblyName/DefaultNamespace) instead of always using the project file name.
- Compilation and parse options are now derived by parsing the compiler command line with Roslyn's own parser - the same approach as MSBuildWorkspace - so defines, language version, unsafe/checked/nullable, optimization, platform, warning level, documentation mode and the full diagnostic configuration (including SDK-injected warnaserror/nowarn defaults) all match the compiler. Reconstruction from MSBuild properties remains as a fallback when no command line was captured.
- Compilation options now carry the same services MSBuildWorkspace attaches: XML/source reference resolvers, a DesktopStrongNameProvider (so signed assemblies can be emitted from the workspace) and DesktopAssemblyIdentityComparer.
- Publish SBOM.
]]>
    </PackageReleaseNotes>
  </PropertyGroup>

  <ItemGroup>
    <PackageReference Include="Microsoft.CodeAnalysis.CSharp.Workspaces" Version="5.6.0" />
    <PackageReference Include="Microsoft.CodeAnalysis.VisualBasic.Workspaces" Version="5.6.0" />
  </ItemGroup>

  <ItemGroup>
    <ProjectReference Include="../Buildalyzer/Buildalyzer.csproj" />
  </ItemGroup>

</Project>
